2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed system can be applied to wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper mentions the use of hypergraphs, which are commonly used in social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed system can be used for multimedia transmission over wireless channels. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the proposed algorithms and their performance in terms of the number of decoding iterations.
